<subSubSection id="2B996578FFDFFFD31ED13FF2FBBAF8F7" pageId="11" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFDFFFD31ED13FF2FE94F889" blockId="11.[189,310,1770,1796]" box="[189,310,1770,1796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="37">
<heading id="3874819FFFDFFFD31ED13FF2FE94F889" bold="true" box="[189,310,1770,1796]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFDFFFD31ED13FF2FE94F889" bold="true" box="[189,310,1770,1796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFDFFFD31ED13E01FBBAF8F7" blockId="11.[189,1399,1817,1914]" pageId="11" pageNumber="37">
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFDFFFD31F363E02FDA2F8BE" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1929" box="[346,512,1817,1843]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrostyla">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFDFFFD31F363E02FDA2F8BE" box="[346,512,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="37">K. macrostyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFDFFFD31C8E3E02FC3AF8BE" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[738,920,1817,1844]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Kryptochroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentacantha">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFDFFFD31C8E3E02FD54F8BE" box="[738,758,1818,1843]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="37">K</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFDFFFD31D6B3E01FC3AF8BE" box="[775,920,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="37">pentacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its robust body and large size when compared to other males of the genus, and by the stout and conical RTA (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFDFFFD31A483E24FB07F8DA" box="[1060,1189,1852,1879]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,234,1953,1982]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1037,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-194@12.[189,1398,1037,1915]" captionText="Fig. 6. Male of Kryptochroma macrostyla (Mello-Leitão, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. (MZSP 15320). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Front. C–F. Left male palp. C, E. Ventral view. D, F. Retrolateral view." pageId="11" pageNumber="37">Figs 6D, F</figureCitation>
, 20C), but can be easily distinguished by their long, free and filiform embolus (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFDFFFD31DE13E47FBA9F8F7" box="[909,1035,1887,1914]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,234,1953,1982]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1037,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-194@12.[189,1398,1037,1915]" captionText="Fig. 6. Male of Kryptochroma macrostyla (Mello-Leitão, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. (MZSP 15320). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Front. C–F. Left male palp. C, E. Ventral view. D, F. Retrolateral view." pageId="11" pageNumber="37">Fig. 6C, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
